{"pageProps":{"article":{"title":"Pesto With A Twist","category":"On the Menu","subcategory":"Recipes","publish_date":"2015-08-07T07:00:00.000Z","full_thumbnail":"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/unnamed.jpg?resize=355%2C230&ssl=1","mobile_thumbnail":"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/unnamed.jpg?resize=980%2C647&ssl=1","description":"A new take on the delicious sauce that is pesto, only this time with asparagus instead of basil, super easy and very yummy","content":"<div class=\"single-post-content\">\n            <div id=\"attachment_64426\" style=\"width: 1034px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/unnamed.jpg\" data-slb-active=\"1\" data-slb-asset=\"1893851266\" data-slb-internal=\"0\" data-slb-group=\"64425\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-64426\" data-attachment-id=\"64426\" data-permalink=\"https://dailynexus.com/2015-08-07/pesto-with-a-twist/processed-with-vscocam-with-g3-preset/\" data-orig-file=\"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/unnamed.jpg?fit=3264%2C2172&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"3264,2172\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta='{\"aperture\":\"0\",\"credit\":\"\",\"camera\":\"\",\"caption\":\"Processed with VSCOcam with g3 preset\",\"created_timestamp\":\"0\",\"copyright\":\"Copyright 2015. All rights reserved.\",\"focal_length\":\"0\",\"iso\":\"0\",\"shutter_speed\":\"0\",\"title\":\"Processed with VSCOcam with g3 preset\",\"orientation\":\"0\"}' data-image-title=\"Processed with VSCOcam with g3 preset\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/unnamed.jpg?fit=250%2C166&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/unnamed.jpg?fit=888%2C591&amp;ssl=1\" class=\"size-large wp-image-64426\" src=\"https://i1.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/unnamed-1024x681.jpg?resize=888%2C591\" alt=\"Pasta with Portobello mushrooms and asparagus pesto Taylor Nguyen/Daily Nexus\" width=\"888\" height=\"591\" srcset=\"https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/unnamed.jpg?resize=1024%2C681&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/unnamed.jpg?resize=250%2C166&amp;ssl=1 250w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/unnamed.jpg?w=1776 1776w, https://i2.wp.com/dailynexus.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/unnamed.jpg?w=2664 2664w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 888px) 100vw, 888px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"></a><p id=\"caption-attachment-64426\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Pasta with portabello mushrooms and asparagus pesto <em>Taylor Nguyen/Daily Nexus</em></p></div>\n<p>Carbs smothered in pesto is a beautiful thing. Being a proud pesto fiend, I am always looking for unique ways to rev it up. Pesto is typically a sauce consisting of olive oil, pine nuts, Parmesan, salt, pepper and the main star, basil. However, I decided to try giving asparagus the spotlight this time. Yes, asparagus. Using one of my favorite veggies in this way gives the pesto a fluffy consistency, creamy taste and vibrant color. I substituted a more typical protein for meaty and delicious portabello mushrooms sautéed in garlic butter. A Parmesan and pine nut garnish finish the dish with beautiful, nutty notes and playful textures. The best part is that the recipe is super simple and tasty; perfect for summer and sure to excite anyone’s taste buds!</p>\n<p>INGREDIENTS</p>\n<ul>\n<li>½ pound of asparagus</li>\n<li>5 cloves of fresh garlic, minced</li>\n<li>½ cup of roasted pine nuts*</li>\n<li>½ cup of Parmesan cheese*</li>\n<li>¾ cup of extra virgin olive oil</li>\n<li>1 pound of pasta of your choice</li>\n<li>2 tbs. butter</li>\n<li>2 large portabello mushrooms, sliced</li>\n<li>1-2 shallots, thinly sliced</li>\n<li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>\n</ul>\n<p>* Roast extra pine nuts and set aside extra Parmesan for topping the 